London dispersion forces arise from temporary, fluctuating dipoles caused by uneven electron distribution in atoms or molecules, not permanent dipoles or other intermolecular forces. These weak, instantaneous attractions occur in all molecules, regardless of polarity. Options like **C** (permanent dipoles) or **J** (polar covalent bonds) describe dipole-dipole interactions, not London forces.
